Class OTUSet

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:

public final class OTUSet
extends PersistentObject

A set of OTUs. The relationship between OTU and OTUSet is many-to-many.

Author:
Shirley Cohen, Sam Donnelly

addOTU

public OTUSet addOTU(OTU otu)
Scaffolding code that does two things:
  1. Adds otu to this OTUSet's constituent OTUs
  2. Adds this OTUSet to otu's OTUSets
So it takes care of both sides of the OTUSet<-> OTU relationship.

otu must not be in a detached state.

otu must have a label that is unique relative to this OTU set.

Parameters:
otu - see description
Returns:
this OTU set
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if this OTU set already has an OTU with otu's label
